                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-19T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 19, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 19—10:40
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3218. The Turkish Ambasador to Germany has been summoned to a consultation
                    outside of Berlin with Hitler and Von Ribbentrop<note n="87" xml:id="d966fn87"
                        >Joachim von Ribbentrop, German Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> to take
                    place today.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Ankara.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
